DESCRIPTION:This simulated experiment examines the composition of atoms\, t
 he stabilities of light element isotopes\, and the structures of simple mo
 lecules. \n\nNOTES:\n\n* You should begin work on this experiment as soon
  as practical\, and should consult me with any questions/etc. at your disc
 retion. Please allow a reasonable amount of time for me to respond to your
  inquiries (typically no longer than one working day). Requesting assistan
 ce on the day the assignment is due is strongly discouraged.\n\n* You may 
 take as much time as needed (prior to the submission deadline) to complete
  this experiment\, but may only "submit" the assignment once.  Informatio
 n you enter will be saved if you leave the assignment page without submitt
 ing.  \n\n* As for all our module experiments\, I will review each stude
 nt's submission after the due date has passed to score any items that are 
 not automatically scored (and to double-check the auto-scored items).  Fi
 nal assignment scores and answer keys/feedback will typically be posted a 
 day or two after the submission due date.
SEQUENCE:0
SUMMARY:module 1 experiment [CHM-1300-900-S26]
URL;VALUE=URI:https://canvas.uncp.edu/calendar?include_contexts=course_3836
 2&month=01&year=2026#assignment_922450
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>This simulated experiment examines the comp
 osition of atoms\, the stabilities of light element isotopes\, and the str
 uctures of simple molecules.&nbsp\;</p>\n<p><em>NOTES:</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li
 ><em>You should begin work on this experiment as soon as practical\, and s
 hould consult me with any questions/etc. at your discretion. Please allow 
 a reasonable amount of time for me to respond to your inquiries (typically
  no longer than one working day). Requesting assistance on the day the ass
 ignment is due is strongly discouraged.</em></li>\n<li><em>You may take as
  much time as needed (prior to the submission deadline) to complete this e
 xperiment\, but may only "submit" the assignment once.&nbsp\; Information 
 you enter will be saved if you leave the assignment page without submittin
 g.&nbsp\;&nbsp\;</em></li>\n<li><em>As for all our module experiments\, I 
 will review each student's submission after the due date has passed to sco
 re any items that are not automatically scored (and to double-check the au
 to-scored items).&nbsp\; Final assignment scores and answer keys/feedback 
 will typically be posted a day or two after the submission due date.</em><
 /li>\n</ul>
END:VEVENT
