 ences each. For instance\, for Q11\, we may state that "Client-server rel
 ies on centralized\, always-on servers with permanent IPs\, while P2P dist
 ributes tasks across peers\, adding scalability but more management comple
 xity."\n\nPlease submit your completed document by Friday\, February 20th
 \, before the class time.\n\nLet me know if you have any questions!\n\nTh
 anks & Regards\,\nZhengkun
