 ith common chemical reactions. \n\nNOTES:\n\n* You should begin work on t
 his experiment as soon as practical\, and should consult me with any quest
 ions/etc. at your discretion. Please allow a reasonable amount of time for
  me to respond to your inquiries (typically no longer than one working day
 ). Requesting assistance on the day the assignment is due is strongly disc
 ouraged.\n\n* You may take as much time as needed (prior to the submission
  deadline) to complete this experiment\, but may only "submit" the assignm
 ent once.  Information you enter will be saved if you leave the assignmen
 t page without submitting.  \n\n* As for all our module experiments\, I 
 will review each student's submission after the due date has passed to sco
 re any items that are not automatically scored (and to double-check the au
 to-scored items).  Final assignment scores and answer keys/feedback will 
 typically be posted a day or two after the submission due date.
